        {
            "_id": "NIM5qaHH7m97CE2t",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Bully the Bully",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Augsten's sense of strength and self-worth shatters whenever someone calls him \"Little Lord Augie.\" A PC can attempt to send Augsten into a tantrum by calling him by this insult as part of a special attempt to [[/act create-a-diversion dc=24 traits=auditory,linguistic]] that has the auditory and linguistic traits, with the following results.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> Augsten is cut deep by your teasing! He becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stunned]{Stunned 1} by his rage, and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Off-Guard] to your attacks for the next 24 hours. During this time, he takes a –4 circumstance penalty to all attempts to use [[/act demoralize]] on any target, and can't use Bullying Command.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Bully the Bully (Critical Success)]</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> Your insult enrages Augsten, causing him to become off-guard to your attacks until the start of his next turn as he's distracted by his anger. The next attempt to insult him using this by any PC gains a +2 circumstance bonus to the Deception check.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> Your attempt fails to rile Augsten up, but it does attract his attention. He focuses his attacks on you on his next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> Your attempt to tease Augsten backfires, and instead of sending him into a sputtering tantrum, you enrage him. He gains a +2 status bonus to all damage rolls against you for the next 24 hours, during which time you cannot attempt to Bully the Bully. Augsten favors you as his target for all attacks during this time.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Bully the Bully (Critical Failure)]</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "auditory",
                        "concentrate",
                        "emotion",
                        "linguistic",
                        "mental"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
